## vim Dockerfile

  FROM  ----->  To mention which base OS you are going to use
  
  RUN   ----->  To run any command during build time(i.e. while creating image)
  
  CMD   ----->  To run any command during run time(i.e. after launching of container)
  
  COPY  ----->  To copy any file from docker host to image
  
  
 ## docker build -t <image_name>:<tag> <location/path>   ----->  TO build the image
 
 ## docker run -it <image_name>:<tag>  ----->  To launch the container
 
 ## docker ps  ----->  To check the status of running containers
 
 ## yum whatprovides <cmd_name>  ----->  To check the software name of that particular command
